06/06/2004
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- The OECD Second Ministerial-level International Conference on small- and medium-size enterprises wrapped up Saturday in Istanbul with participants issuing a final statement.
It underscored the importance of the new initiative launched by Turkey and supported by Brazil, Italy and Portugal, among others.
The Emerging Regional Markets Technology Transfer Network aims to support the process of globalisation and liberalisation of economies in countries with emerging markets.
(Anadolu Agency, TRT 2, NTV - 05/06/04)
